<h2>‚úÖ Direct Intervention</h2>

You walk up to them at the base of the stairs.

<strong>You say:</strong> "Hey! I think your friends were looking for you downstairs. Want to come hang with us?"

The intoxicated person looks relieved and says "Oh yeah, okay." The other person looks annoyed but backs off.

<div class="feedback-box">
<h3>üí™ Why This Worked:</h3>
<strong>‚úì Direct but non-confrontational:</strong> You intervened without accusing anyone

<strong>‚úì Gave an "out":</strong> Provided an easy, face-saving exit

<strong>‚úì Friendly tone:</strong> Didn't escalate the situation

<strong>‚úì Quick action:</strong> Intervened before they went upstairs

<h4>Key Phrases That Work:</h4>
- "Your friends are looking for you"
- "Can I talk to you for a second?"
- "Do you know where [bathroom/exit] is?"
- "I think you dropped something downstairs"

<h4>Remember:</h4>
Trust your instincts. If someone seems too intoxicated to consent, that's a red flag worth acting on.
</div>

<strong>Skill Earned:</strong> Direct Intervention ‚≠ê

