### **Passage: Get Help Path**

**Passage Name:** S1 Get Help


(set: $skills to $skills via "directIntervention", it + 1)
(set: $skills to $skills via "warningSigns", it + 1)

<h2>‚úÖ Delegated Intervention</h2>

You quickly grab two friends from your group and explain what you saw.

<strong>You say:</strong> "That person by the stairs looks really drunk and is being led upstairs. Can you help me check on them?"

With three of you, you approach and your friend says, "Hey, we're heading out soon. Want to come with us to get food?"

The intoxicated person agrees, and your group helps them get water and call a ride home.

<div class="feedback-box">
<h3>üí™ Why This Worked:</h3>

<strong>‚úì Safety in numbers:</strong> Multiple people are less threatening and more effective

<strong>‚úì Distributed responsibility:</strong> Not all on you alone

<strong>‚úì More options:</strong> Different people can take different roles

<strong>‚úì Social proof:</strong> Harder for others to dismiss multiple people's concerns

<h4>Who Can You Get Help From:</h4>
- Friends in your group
- Party host
- Resident advisor (if on campus)
- Sober monitor (if there is one)
- Security or staff (at venues)

<h4>What to Say:</h4>
- "I'm worried about that person - can you help?"
- "I think we should check on them"
- "This doesn't feel right to me"

<h4>Remember:</h4>
Getting help is smart, not cowardly. Bystander intervention is more effective with multiple people.
</div>

<strong>Skill Earned:</strong> Direct Intervention ‚≠ê

