### Passage: Observe Path

Passage Name: S1 Observe

(set: $skills to $skills via "warningSigns", it + 1)

<h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Observing the Situation</h2>

You watch for a moment to assess. The intoxicated person stumbles on the first stair. The other person catches them but continues leading them upward.

As you watch, they disappear into a room upstairs. You're now uncertain what's happening and the moment for easy intervention has passed.

<div class="feedback-box">
<h3>ü§î What Happened Here:</h3>

<strong>Why observation alone wasn't enough:</strong>

‚úó Window for intervention closed quickly
‚úó Person potentially in unsafe situation now
‚úó Harder to intervene once they're in a private space
‚úó You'd need to go upstairs, which is more confrontational

<h4>When Observation IS Useful:</h4>
- To gather information before acting
- To identify the best approach
- To see if others are already helping
- <strong>But should be BRIEF (seconds, not minutes)</strong>

<h4>What You Could Do Now:</h4>

[[Go upstairs and knock on doors to check->S1 Observe Late Intervention]]

[[Tell the party host what you saw->S1 Observe Tell Host]]

[[Stay alert and check if they come back down->S1 Observe Wait]]

</div>

<strong>Learning Point:</strong> Trust your instincts and act quickly. Concern for safety > fear of awkwardness.


